com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.name: Symlinks could be messed up
com.sonyericsson.jenkins.plugins.bfa.mod.description:
This one is specific to Shelves.CleanOld job.
Look for an null exception in Jenkins Log ( not this job log)
If found log on at Jenkins Master host, and browse to the job folder of the job which we are trying to shelve. Look for .symlink file, with zero byte length - and delete them.
The bold stop Jenkins service, run this powershell shell snippet Get-ChildItem -Path E:\JenkinsData\jobs -recurse -force | Where-Object {$_.LinkType -eq 'SymbolicLink' -and $_.Length -eq 0} | Remove-Item and start the service again.
